%N A081357 Sublime numbers, numbers for which the number of divisors and the sum of the divisors are both perfect.
%C A081357 The concept was introduced and the term "sublime numbers" was coined by Kevin Brown. a(1) was found by Brown (1995) and a(2) by Hickerson (1995). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 26 2021
%C A081357 a(2) = 2^126 * M(3) * M(5) * M(7) * M(19) * M(31) * M(61), where M(n) = 2^n - 1. - _Lucas A. Brown_, Mar 05 2025
%C A081357 It is known that all sublime numbers must be of that form, with all odd prime factors being Mersenne primes M(p). - _M. F. Hasler_, Mar 05 2025
